commit.message:
Return date in (#91)

* stopped running tests on prod, because there have been quite a few times where maven on AWS freezes up, not super clear why, possibly too much memory usage but it's hard to tell TBH
* made a NewTokens object so it could be returned with XML, but TBH, it's not super useful, because it adds extra layers to the JSON that I can't really get rid of. Should reconsider all possible targets
* explicitly don't add Timezones to Date, which Tyler doesn't seem to like, despite it being allowed in XML (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6143224/how-do-i-represent-dates-without-the-timezone-using-apache-cxf)
* lets you add and set attorneys from existing users
* don't crash if media type isn't passed
* Need to check if things are numbers, not BigDecimal
* Amount in controversy not always supported
